Got it ‚Äî now the rule is very specific:

üéØ FINAL BEHAVIOR YOU WANT

‚úÖ Content should NOT be visible when it scrolls under the header

(because header is solid + fixed)

‚úÖ BUT content should remain visible when it scrolls under the floating button

(floating button should NOT hide content under it)

So the header must cover content.

The floating button must not cover content.

This is easy:

üëâ The header stays on top with a real opaque background
üëâ The floating button must not block content, so it must have pointer-events: none EXCEPT the button itself.
üëâ The floating button must have transparent background or small size so content shows behind it.

I will now send your updated working files.


